        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Richmond <sic>va.</sic></placeName>
                <date>March the 8. 5618</date>.</p>
            <p>To the Editor of the Occident Rev. <addressee>Mr. I. Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Rev. Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">It may not be uninteresting to you to receive<lb/> an account of the
                progress and <sic>wellfare</sic> of the Congregation<lb/> “Benesseth Israel” formed
                about 18 months ago in this City.<lb/> The Minhag is the <sic>polish</sic> one, upon
                the most orthodox princip<lb/>les. Our progress has been gradual and steady, and I
                am happy<lb/> to inform you, that we were enabled to consecrate a beautiful<lb/>
                “Sephar Tora” last <date><sic>monday</sic></date>, <add>Hebrew</add>, through the
                beneficence of<lb/>
                <persName>Mr. Louis Cohn</persName>, who had it <sic>writen</sic> especially for him
                in <placeName>Europe</placeName>.<lb/>
                <persName>Mr. F. Bendann</persName> officiated in the Camonics<add>?</add> usual
                upon such<lb/> occasion and the <persName>Rev. Mr Michelbach</persName> of the
                    <sic>german</sic> Cong. delivered<lb/> an appropriate address. In a short time
                the Cong. expects<lb/> to be enabled to remove to a more enlarged and
                convenient<lb/> place of worship, which will no doubt conduce to their<lb/>
                prosperity and advancement.</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">Yours respectfully and truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">
                <persName role="author">F. Bendani</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
